cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing tasks such as dependency parsing. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes a hybrid approach that combines rule-based and morphological information with deep learning. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper proposes methods to improve the accuracy of neural parsers through the integration of explicit knowledge about the target language. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible category as the paper deals with deep learning-based models. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a less likely category as the paper does not focus on developing new algorithms or data structures, but rather on improving the performance of existing models through the integration of additional information.
